1
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:10,100
♪I love the clarity in your eyes♪

2
00:00:10,740 --> 00:00:13,860
♪Like a shooting star across my world♪

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,580
♪Repeating the goodbye we never said♪

4
00:00:18,260 --> 00:00:21,540
♪Through sleepless nights♪

5
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:25,100
♪I miss the way you looked at me♪

6
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:30,260
♪Like photos freezing that summer bit by bit♪

7
00:00:30,660 --> 00:00:35,380
♪By the shore with warm winds, maybe we'll meet again♪

8
00:00:37,380 --> 00:00:41,460
[Fall in Love Again]

9
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:43,980
[Episode 20]

10
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:50,280
How's your leg? Feeling better?

11
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:52,560
I'm fine now.

12
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:54,640
Don't run off like that again.

13
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:56,040
Okay.

14
00:00:57,760 --> 00:00:59,640
Entertainment News reports that recently,

15
00:00:59,720 --> 00:01:01,000
well-known director Qi Siqin

16
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,680
publicly lashed out at his ex-wife, Chu Jingxi,

17
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:04,590
calling her upcoming drama "trash".

18
00:01:05,310 --> 00:01:06,400
Don't listen to their nonsense.

19
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:10,360
Get me in touch with Yang.

20
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:11,960
I want to hold a press conference.

21
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:13,680
A press conference?

22
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:15,000
Some things,

23
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,120
I need to face on my own.

24
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:19,720
Okay.

25
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:21,040
Yang,

26
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,520
I've found Chu.

27
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:24,480
We're holding a press conference this afternoon.

28
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:28,580
[Chu Jingxi Press Conference]

29
00:01:28,580 --> 00:01:30,220
This has really blown up.

30
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:30,820
Seriously.

31
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:34,600
[Tang Hongmei, Xiang Wentian]
Fans never expected photos like this.

32
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:38,080
Is the aperture set?

33
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:39,200
She's coming out soon.

34
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:40,280
- Shoot her as much as you can. - Yeah.

35
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:42,760
Where do they get the nerve

36
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:44,120
after everything she's been through?

37
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:45,840
Guess the saying's true.

38
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,160
You don't play tough, you don't survive.

39
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:49,200
After something like this,

40
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,240
she can still stay that calm.

41
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:51,240
That takes guts.

42
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,880
I couldn't do it myself.

43
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:55,200
Let's hear what she has to say.

44
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,600
We're all here.

45
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,480
Don't be afraid.

46
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:22,560
Where's He Zheng?

47
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,480
I have no idea.

48
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:31,320
Look!

49
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,280
Chu Jingxi's here.

50
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:35,360
- Come on. - Come on.

51
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:36,920
- Over here. - Over here.

52
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:37,920
Ms. Chu.

53
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,800
- Ms. Chu. - Ms. Chu.

54
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:40,960
Ms. Chu, say something.

55
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:41,920
Ms. Chu, please respond.

56
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:43,080
Are those statements true?

57
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:43,800
Please respond.

58
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,080
- Ms. Chu. - Ms. Chu.

59
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,080
Please say something.

60
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,440
- Ms. Chu. - Ms. Chu.

61
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:50,720
Where have you been these days?

62
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:52,560
Are the photos real?

63
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,200
- Ms. Chu. - Ms. Chu.

64
00:02:57,820 --> 00:02:59,080
Yes, please respond.

65
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,680
Did you offend someone?

66
00:03:03,180 --> 00:03:05,360
[Chu Jingxi Press Conference]

67
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:09,600
Thank you all for coming despite your busy schedules.

68
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,160
I appreciate you being here today.

69
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,400
Recent personal matters involving me

70
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:17,480
have drawn widespread attention and discussion.

71
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:20,200
I regret taking up so much public attention,

72
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,440
and I sincerely apologize.

73
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:23,840
That's why I chose to stand here today,

74
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,160
to address these questions head-on.

75
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,160
I want to clear the doubts,

76
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:31,120
and be responsible to myself,

77
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:34,480
my fans, and those who care about me.

78
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:36,800
Ms. Chu, are you the person in the leaked photos?

79
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:38,120
Is that really you?

80
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:41,400
Yes, that is me.

81
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,840
- It really is her. - It really is her.

82
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:46,760
Can you explain

83
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,880
why those photos were taken back then?

84
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:50,160
Those photos

85
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,960
were private memories from when I was with my then-boyfriend.

86
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:56,680
I never imagined they would be leaked.

87
00:03:57,120 --> 00:04:00,040
This is a serious violation of my privacy.

88
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:03,680
I am currently cooperating with the police investigation.

89
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:06,280
Your former public boyfriend was Qi Siqin.

90
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:08,760
Does that mean he's involved in the leak?

91
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:12,160
The case is still under investigation.

92
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,960
We will wait for the official results.

93
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:17,040
Since returning to the industry,

94
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:18,880
controversies seem to follow you constantly.

95
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:21,440
Is this deliberate publicity?

96
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:22,920
As an actress,

97
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:25,480
I'm confident in my acting abilities.

98
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:28,680
If people know me through my work,

99
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:31,960
I accept

100
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,480
both criticism and praise.

101
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,040
But as a woman,

102
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,760
I don't believe personal matters

103
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,840
should be used as promotion.

104
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:46,400
You've been out of the spotlight for nearly four years.

105
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:47,840
After being dumped by your ex,

106
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:49,040
you returned quickly.

107
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,520
Wasn't this for attention?

108
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,920
After all, controversy brings traffic.

109
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:58,680
My return isn't for hype.

110
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:03,080
It's my passion for acting.

111
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,440
True artistic value

112
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,760
doesn't rely on negativity.

113
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:12,040
My goal is to earn recognition

114
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,240
through talent and hard work,

115
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,120
not through so-called scandal fame.

116
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,920
After this period of reflection,

117
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:19,440
the photos are already widespread.

118
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:22,200
Will you continue appearing on screen

119
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,600
and pursue your acting career?

120
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:26,200
I chose to stand here today

121
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:27,960
and answer everyone directly.

122
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:30,440
That is my clearest answer.

123
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:33,680
Chu.

124
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,280
It takes courage to face this.

125
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,480
That alone is admirable.

126
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:39,400
Stay strong, Ms. Chu!

127
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:44,880
Stay strong!

128
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,080
Where did you go?

129
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:56,080
Ms. Chu's strength and courage

130
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,920
have deeply inspired many women.

131
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,680
You've set an example for us.

132
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,520
When facing hardship and challenges,

133
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:04,000
no matter how the world judges us,

134
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,160
we have the right to protect our dignity

135
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,480
and pursue our dreams.

136
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:11,240
Everyone faces setbacks in life.

137
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,720
I'm no exception.

138
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:15,840
Over the past few days,

139
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:18,360
I've been struggling with my own vulnerability.

140
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,720
I tried shutting myself off,

141
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,240
trying to escape reality.

142
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,760
But then I realized

143
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:29,400
there are many women like me

144
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,600
who've been treated unfairly.

145
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,880
We are the victims,

146
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:36,440
yet we're often blamed even more.

147
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,280
I stand here today

148
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:40,360
not just to defend my own rights,

149
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,960
but to let women

150
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:44,240
like me—other victims—know,

151
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,760
through my actions,

152
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,560
that a rose has thorns

153
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:51,120
because it was once

154
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:53,400
deeply hurt.

155
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,520
This experience

156
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,760
has taught me to cherish every chance,

157
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,120
and be grateful for everyone around me.

158
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:05,920
Thank you all.

159
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,600
Congratulations.

160
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,320
Like a butterfly reborn.

161
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,480
What's there to watch in gossip like this?

162
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:29,720
I'm just curious.

163
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,400
How does she even bear it?

164
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,360
What does she have to do with you?

165
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,640
Clean yourself up. There's a dinner tonight.

166
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,520
Qi Siqin.

167
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,000
Who do you think I am?

168
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,960
Who you are doesn't matter.

169
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:43,720
Just keep Mr. Zheng happy tonight.

170
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,840
He's very interested in my project.

171
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,160
I'm pregnant.

172
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,760
After tonight's dinner,

173
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:58,720
go to the hospital tomorrow and get rid of it.

174
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:01,960
You're inhuman.

175
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,040
You're going tonight. No excuses.

176
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:07,840
I'm not going.

177
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,880
Have I been too nice to you?

178
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:19,120
I'm not asking you.

179
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:28,920
Chu,

180
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,600
you were amazing.

181
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,400
Thanks.

182
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,240
You were amazing.

183
00:08:40,030 --> 00:08:41,720
Why did you come dressed like this?

184
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:54,680
I hope that in the future,

185
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,920
I won't only protect you on screen.

186
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,480
For the rest of your life,

187
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:01,360
I'll be the one protecting you too.

188
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,640
There are reporters.

189
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,280
You two really know how to stir things up.

190
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:30,880
So you think you can give me attitude?

191
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,760
You think that's okay with me?

192
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,080
Lin Yu, you'd better listen.

193
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:37,480
If you want to stay in this business,

194
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:39,240
you do what I say.

195
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:41,480
What happened today...

196
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:44,160
I don't want to see it again!

197
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,440
Qi Siqin, I'm done with you.

198
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,240
I'm leaving you!

199
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:57,160
Leave me?

200
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,000
Only if you're dead!

201
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:06,680
Now figure out how to keep Mr. Zheng happy!

202
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:54,040
♪When clouds sink into the deep sea♪

203
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:57,320
♪Ripples spread♪

204
00:10:57,960 --> 00:11:00,400
♪Traces of a racing heart♪

205
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:03,880
♪Is it the sky or its reflection♪

206
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:07,360
♪I can't tell anymore♪

207
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:11,680
♪Lost in your eyes♪

208
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:17,200
♪As we draw closer♪

209
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,360
♪The space of an embrace♪

210
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:23,560
♪Scatters the dark♪

211
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:27,840
♪When the wind comes, raise the sails♪

212
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,120
♪And sail on♪

213
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:35,680
♪Miles ahead are no longer a dream♪

214
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:41,560
♪Where even migratory birds can't reach, you're by my side♪

215
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:47,360
♪Then I can spread my wings and fly with courage♪

216
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:53,120
♪If storms rise, I'll follow your light♪

217
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:58,960
♪Trusting we'll reach a warm shore♪

218
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:04,720
♪Where even migratory birds can't reach, you're by my side♪

219
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:11,200
♪I'll break through the haze and run toward what I once longed for♪

220
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:16,240
♪Even if I'm hurt, I won't wander alone♪

221
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:20,640
♪You're where my heart belongs♪

222
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:38,040
♪As we draw closer♪

223
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:41,560
♪The space of an embrace♪

224
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:44,240
♪Scatters the dark♪

225
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:48,760
♪When the wind comes, raise the sails♪

226
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:51,800
♪And sail on♪

227
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:56,600
♪Miles ahead are no longer a dream♪

228
00:12:57,560 --> 00:13:02,600
♪Where even migratory birds can't reach, you're by my side♪

229
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:08,320
♪Then I can spread my wings and fly with courage♪

230
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:14,160
♪If storms rise, I'll follow your light♪

231
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:19,840
♪Trusting we'll reach a warm shore♪

232
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:25,680
♪Where even migratory birds can't reach, you're by my side♪

233
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:32,120
♪I'll break through the haze and run toward what I once longed for♪

234
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:37,280
♪Even if I'm hurt, I won't wander alone♪

235
